Cell["\<\
Note that since Mathematica didn\[CloseCurlyQuote]t actually evaluate my \
function definition when I defined it, there is no output until I call the \
function in the second cell block. There are advantages and disadvantages to \
using  = and :=.  You will get a better feeling for them as \
\>", "Text",
